content.description: Low start under small roof. Make a few moves (careful not to slip into water below) making your way up an easy juggy arête.
content.location: Small overhung roof that leads out of the creeks small rapid waterfall. Just behind Wolf Den. Careful not to fall into the water.

content.description:
Shaded area, because of the overhang. Gets a good amount of sun. The rock is good here, but it definitely needs a good dry  week to climb this area. 

  There has been one documented ascent in this section, on the overhang, but no named attached to the ascent. 

  No information about the actual name of this area, so I will leave the name standing, until I find out more.
